### splitTwoPartImm() {#a92e31a04c0a1b5d17db90c99fa48f6aa}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;typename T&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>bool anonymous&#95;namespace&#123;AArch64MIPeepholeOpt.cpp&#125;::AArch64MIPeepholeOpt::splitTwoPartImm (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineinstr">MachineInstr</a> &amp; MI, <a href="#abc1a6dd133078668947d5536e70ea6eb">SplitAndOpcFunc</a>&lt; T &gt; SplitAndOpc, <a href="#a3a5aae95c739a79a3ae6145a55cdef27">BuildMIFunc</a> BuildInstr)</>}>
For instructions where an immediate operand could be split into two separate immediate instructions, use the splitTwoPartImm two handle the optimization.

To implement, the following function types must be passed to splitTwoPartImm. A <a href="#abc1a6dd133078668947d5536e70ea6eb">SplitAndOpcFunc</a> must be implemented that determines if splitting the immediate is valid and returns the associated new opcode. A <a href="#a3a5aae95c739a79a3ae6145a55cdef27">BuildMIFunc</a> must be implemented to build the two immediate instructions.

Example <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/pattern">Pattern</a> (where IMM would require 2+ MOV instructions): dst = &lt;Instr&gt;rr src IMM &#91;...&#93; becomes: tmp = &lt;Instr&gt;ri src (encode half IMM) &#91;...&#93; dst = &lt;Instr&gt;ri tmp (encode half IMM) &#91;...&#93;

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64mipeepholeopt-cpp/#l00119">119</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64mipeepholeopt-cpp">AArch64MIPeepholeOpt.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
